name: pregy
label: Mother: Pregnant When Had Personal Interview, year
description: Note that the information concerning year and month of birth from the “Mother & Child” and “Parent” questionnaires proved to be partially inconsistent. Therefore, as of the beginning of 2012 the child’s age in months is computed using birth information from ppfad. For further information, refer to the documentation on ppfad. Furthermore, this question is only asked in bioage01.

name: pregmo
label: mother: month of pregnancy at individual interview
description: This variable is based on the exact month of birth (BCPREGMO), the duration of childbearing in weeks (BCSSW) and the interview month of the previous year’s personal interview. Hence this information is available only for those women in the sample for at least two years. As the exact day of birth is unknown, this variable remains a close approximation. Furthermore, this question is only asked in bioage01.

name: prebeg
label: Spell Start Pregnancy(Month,01.83=1)
description: The variable BCPREBEG contains information on the beginning of pregnancy (i.e., the month of conception). Information is given in the regular SOEP spell format: values start with 1 for January 1983 (e.g., the earliest spell in bioage01, survey year 2010, is 304, which equals April 2008). Furthermore, this question is only asked in bioage01.

name: preend
label: spell end of pregnancy, birth
description: The variable is based on the exact month of birth (BCPREGMO) and the duration of pregnancy in weeks (BCSSW). Accordingly, information is available only for women who completed the “Mother & Child Questionnaire” and for whom the duration of the pregnancy is known. Note that the month of conception may vary by one month as the exact date of birth remains unknown. Furthermore, this question is only asked in bioage01.

description: Please find detailed information in PDF documentation.

name: bio
label: Form Of Biography Questionnaire
description: Since 2008 the variable BIO is generated to indicate the origin of the information in BIOPAREN (Biography or Youth Questionnaire). This information is valid for all cases from 2001 onwards.

name: alter
label: Age
description: See description of MALTER.

name: valter
label: Age Father
description: See description of MALTER.

name: malter
label: Age Mother
description:
Since 2008 the variables ALTER, VALTER and MALTER were added to BIOPAREN. 
The variable ALTER gives the age of the respondent at the moment of the interview. VALTER gives the age of the respondents’ father when the respondent answered the Biography Questionnaire or the Youth Questionnaire. The same was applied for the mothers with the variable MALTER. In order to generate the variables the information for the parents who are identified in the SOEP was gained with data from PPFAD. The proxy entries from BIOPAREN were used when there weren’t any information of the respondents parents available.

name: vgebj
label: Year Of Birth Father
description: See description of MGEBJ.

name: mgebj
label: Year Of Birth Mother
description:
In a first step, the information of the year of birth comes from the Biography Questionnaire. Due to a filter command, the children’s proxy entries are only available for these variables when the parents or one parent and the child do not live in the same household at the time of the survey. 
After the parents’ personal numbers have been identified the information can be compared with the entries in PPFAD. If there are differences of +/- two years the FPID / MPID will be set as missing. 
For the missing entries the information of the parents’ year of birth is taken from PPFAD.

name: vtodj
label: Year Of Death Father
description: See description of MTODJ.

name: mtodj
label: Year Of Death Mother
description: Please find detailed information in PDF documentation.

name: vsbil
label: Level Of Education Father
description: See description of MSBIL.

name: msbil
label: Level Of Education Mother
description:
The parents’ education is generated with information from the Youth Questionnaire, the Biography Questionnaire and direct entries from the PGEN-files. Due to the filter command, the children’s proxy entries are only available for VSBIL / MSBIL when the parents or one parent and the child do not live in the same household at the time of the survey. 
Along with other variables already contained in BIOPAREN, there will be an update with new survey information, insofar as no valid values exist in BIOPAREN.

name: vsinfo
label: Origin SBIL Father
description: See description of MSINFO.

name: mnat
label: Nationality of Mother
description: The question is only asked to youngsters who are not living in the same household as their parents. PGEN information is used to compute a variable with data from 2006 onwards. In a further step the parents’ personal numbers are used to match information on parents’ nationality with data from the PGEN-files in the case if there are missing entries.

name: vorigin
label: Country of Origin, Father
description: See description of MORIGIN.

name: morigin
label: Country of Origin, Mother
description: These variables give information about the country of origin of the respondents mother (MORIGIN) and father (VORIGIN). This information is collected in the Youth Questionnaires since 2007. Another source of information can be found in PPFAD by the direct-entries of the parents in the variable CORIGIN. These two kinds of information, proxy- and direct-entries, are used to generate MORIGIN and VORIGIN. In a first step we use the proxy-information for all the parents whose children made an entry in the Youth Questionnaire. For all the parents where there are no proxy-information available, we then use the direct-entries of the parents from the PPFAD-variable CORIGIN.

name: vreli
label: Religion Father
description: See description of MRELI.

name: mreli
label: Religion Mother
description: The questions about the religious affiliation of the parents are only asked to youngsters who are not living in the household of their parents. In order to provide as much information as possible we gather data from the Personal Questionnaires. The reconstruction of the information on the parents’ religion is restricted to the survey years 1997, 2003 and 2007 as they are the only years where information of a respondent’s religious affiliation is available. In all survey years the question was formulated differently but the information is made as consistent as possible.

name: vbstell
label: Job Position Father
description: See description of MBSTELL.

name: mbstell
label: Job Position Mother
description:
The children’s proxy entries on professional position and occupation of the father (VBSTELL) as well as VISCO88 and all prestige scores are available when the father and the child do not live in the same household at the time of the survey and if the father lived in Germany when the child was 16 years old. Since 2000, the same applies to the entries of the mother for MVSTELL and MISCO88. 
Besides the proxy entries parents’ direct information from the $P-files are used.

name: vbsinfo
label: Origin VBSTELL Father
description: See description of MBSINFO.

name: mbsinfo
label: Origin VBSTELL Mother
description: The variables VBSINFO / MBSINFO are indicator variables. They tell whether the information is from the Biography or Youth or Personal Questionnaires. This information is generated at the same steps as it is done with the VBSTELL / MBSTELL variables.

name: vbklas92
label: FATHER: Current Occupational Classification (KldB92)
description:
This variable is designed to provide data on job classification for fathers according to the classification of the German Federal Statistical Office (StaBuA) from 1992. The recoding has been documented in Hartmann/Schütz 2002.

In the SOEP-IS, vbklas92 is released up until 2016 and coded to [-5] afterwards. Starting in 2017, only vbklas10 scores will be released.

name: mbklas92
label: MOTHER: Current Occupational Classification (KldB92)
description:
This variable is designed to provide data on job classification for mothers according to the classification of the German Federal Statistical Office (StaBuA) from1992. The recoding has been documented in Hartmann/Schütz 2002.
 
In the SOEP-IS, mbklas92 is released up until 2016 and coded to [-5] afterwards. Starting in 2017, only mbklas10 scores will be released.

name: vbklas10
label: FATHER: Current Occupational Classification (KldB2010)
description:
This variable is designed to provide data on job classification for fathers according to the classification of the German Federal Statistical Office (StaBuA) from 2010. 

In the SOEP-IS, vbklas10 was first implemented in wave 2016 and is coded [-5] in all previous waves.

German Classification of Occupations 2010. https://statistik.arbeitsagentur.de/Navigation/Statistik/Grundlagen/Klassifikation-der-Berufe/KldB2010/Arbeitshilfen/EnglischeKldB2010/KldBEnglischl-Nav.html

In the SOEP-IS, mbklas10 was first implemented in wave 2016 and is coded [-5] in all previous waves.

name: vmps92
label: FATHER: Magnitude Prestige Scale (based on KldB92)
description: See description of MMPS92.

name: mmps92
label: MOTHER: Magnitude Prestige Scale (based on KldB92)
description:
These variables give the occupational prestige score developed by Wegener (1988) for fathers and mothers. Like the SIOPS prestige sore, Wegener’s prestige scala measures a person’s occupational prestige and was developed especially for use in the Federal Republic of Germany. MPS is assigned based on the German Federal Statistical Office’s occupational classification of 1992 (KLAS). The procedure has been documented in Frietsch and Wirth (2001).

In the SOEP-IS, vmps92 & mmps92 are released up until 2016 and coded to [-5] afterwards. Starting in 2017, only vmps08 & mmps08 scores will be released.

name: vmps08
label: FATHER: Magnitude Prestige Scale (based on IS88 recoded from IS08)
label_de: VATER: Magnitude Prestigeskala (based on IS88 recoded from IS08)
description: See description of MMPS08.

name: mmps08
label: MOTHER: Magnitude Prestige Scale (based on IS88 recoded from IS08)
label_de: MUTTER: Magnitude Prestigeskala (based on IS88 recoded from IS08)
description:
The Magnitude-Prestige-Scale (MPS) is a tool for operationalising the social position of occupations in empirical surveys. In contrast to alternative instruments such as the Standard International Occupational Prestige Scale (SIOPS) or the International Socio-economic Index of Occupational Status (ISEI), the MPS is an instrument that was constructed for analyses on the national level only (Christoph, 2005). Starting in SOEP-IS wave 2016, mps08 is derived from ISCO-88 scores that themselves are derived from ISCO-08 scores using the „derivescores“ STATA package (https://github.com/dirtyhawk/stata-derivescores).

In the SOEP-IS, vmps08 & mmps08 were first implemented in wave 2016 and are coded [-5] in all previous waves.

name: vsiops88

label_de: VATER: TREIMANS STANDARD INT.OCC.PR.SCORE (based on IS88)
description: See description of MSIOPS88.

name: msiops88
label: MOTHER: TREIMANS STANDARD INT.OCC.PR.SCORE (based on IS88)
label_de: MUTTER: TREIMANS STANDARD INT.OCC.PR.SCORE (based on IS88)
description:
These variables give the occupational prestige score index for fathers and mothers. SIOPS is based on ISCO-88 and was developed by Donald Treiman et al. The scale ranges from 6 to 78.

In the SOEP-IS, vsiops88 & msiops88 are released up until 2016 and coded to [-5] afterwards. Starting in 2017, only vsiops08 & msiops08 scores will be released.

name: vsiops08

label_de: VATER: TREIMANS STANDARD INT.OCC.PR.SCORE (based on IS08)
description: See description of MSIOPS08.

name: msiops08
label: MOTHER: TREIMANS STANDARD INT.OCC.PR.SCORE (based on IS08)
label_de: MUTTER: TREIMANS STANDARD INT.OCC.PR.SCORE (based on IS08)
description:
These variables give the occupational prestige score index for fathers and mothers. SIOPS is based on ISCO-88 and was developed by Donald Treiman et al. The scale ranges from 6 to 78. Starting in SOEP-IS wave 2016, vsiops08 & msiops08 are derived from ISCO-88 scores that themselves are derived from ISCO-08 scores using the „derivescores“ STATA package (https://github.com/dirtyhawk/stata-derivescores). This recoding is derived from Ganzeboom‘s SPSS script iskotrei.sps. (http://www.harryganzeboom.nl/isco88/index.htm). 

In the SOEP-IS, vsiops08 & msiops08 were first implemented in wave 2016 and are coded [-5] in all previous waves.

name: megp88
label: MOTHER: ERIKSON and GOLDTHORPE Class Category (based on IS88)
label_de: MUTTER: ERIKSON and GOLDTHORPE Class Category (based on IS88)
description:
These variables give the occupational class for fathers and mothers. EGP is derived from the Standard International Socio-Economic Index of Occupational Status (ISEI). Technically, the variable was created by scaling the ISCO-88 classification. The EGP Index was documented by Ganzeboom/Treiman in 1996 and revised in 2003.

In the SOEP-IS, vegp88 & megp88 are released up until 2016 and coded to [-5] afterwards. Starting in 2017, only vegp08 & megp08 scores will be released.

name: vegp08
label: FATHER: ERIKSON and GOLDTHORPE Class Category (based on IS88 recoded from IS08)

name: megp08
label: MOTHER: ERIKSON and GOLDTHORPE Class Category (based on IS88 recoded from IS08)
label_de: MUTTER: ERIKSON and GOLDTHORPE Class Category (based on IS88 recoded from IS08)
description:
These variables give the occupational class for fathers and mothers. EGP is derived from the Standard International Socio-Economic Index of Occupational Status (ISEI). Technically, the variable was created by scaling the ISCO-88 classification. The EGP Index was documented by Ganzeboom/Treiman in 1996 and revised in 2003. Starting in SOEP-IS wave 2016, vegp08 & megp08 are derived from ISCO-88 scores that themselves are derived from ISCO-08 scores using the „derivescores“ STATA package (https://github.com/dirtyhawk/stata-derivescores). This version of Goldthorpe‘s class categories (EGP) is derived from Ganzeboom‘s SPSS script iskoegp.sps.

In the SOEP-IS, vegp08 & megp08 were first implemented in wave 2016 and are coded [-5] in all previous waves.

name: maortakt
label: Current residence of Mother
description:
The variables VAORTAKT and MAORTAKT contain the latest available information about the parents’ residence and on whether or not they are deceased, respectively. 
For persons without identified parents who answered the biography questionnaire up to the year 2011, the most recent available information from the Personal Questionnaire in, 2001, 2006 or 2011 was assumed. 
For those persons whose parents are identified in the SOEP, the information on the year of death in PPFAD was used for updating. If the year of death lies chronologically after the latest available information, VAORTAKT and MAORTAKT were put on “Has Died”.

name: hgmoveyr
label: Year Moved Into Dwelling
description:
For old households at their old address, data is carried forward for up to two waves. For new households in SOEP and for old households that have moved, the variable is based on newly collected data. In case the information is missing and an old household has moved that year or the previous year, HGMOVEYR is given the value of the year of the respective wave.

 The carrying forward of data entails the possibility that the year of moving into the new dwelling may lie before the year of birth of the oldest household member.

name: hgowner
label: Tenant Or Owner Of Dwelling
description: In all waves, codes 1 and 4 are used if the original variable is coded as -1 (“no answer”) but if at least one answer that is specific to owners, respectively to tenants, was given. Code 4 is also used if a change in ownership (from owner to tenant) has taken place, but no original information for HGOWNER was given.

name: hgacquis
label: Means Of Acquiring Dwelling
description:
Statement by respondent (household head). If no new information is provided and a change of address or ownership status (HGOWNER) has not taken place, the information of the previous year is carried forward.

This information is not assessed in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample from 2012 on, therefore this variable is not generated for these years and coded to "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: hgsubsid
label: Government Subsidizes Housing Payments
description: Statement by respondent. HGSUBSID contains information on government subsidies at the time the housing was built or bought. Information is carried forward until the year 1999.

name: hgosubs
label: Amount Of Subsidies Last Year
label_de: Förderung mit öff. Darlehen letztes Jahr
description:
Statement by respondent. HGOSUBS contains information on cash housing subsidies received from the government during the year prior to the interview. Information is not carried forward.

This information is not assessed in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample from 2012 on, therefore this variable is not generated for these years and coded to "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: hgreval
label: Rent Of Dwelling Vs Comparable Dwellings
description:
Subjective assessment by respondent (household head). The corresponding information from the previous year is not carried forward longitudinally due to the possibility of changes in rent and income, residential moves, and change in the person responding.

This information is not assessed in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample from 2012 on, therefore this variable is not generated for these years and coded to "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: hgrsubs
label: Government Subsidized Housing
description: This information is not assessed in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample from 2012 on, therefore this variable is not generated for these years and coded to "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: hgreduc
label: Dwelling At A Reduced Prize
description:
Information is carried forward from the previous years for
 old households residing at their old address; for new
 households and for old households that have moved, newly
 collected data is used.

This information is not assessed in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample from 2012 on, therefore this variable is not generated for these years and coded to "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: hgsize
label: Size of Housing Unit in Square Meters
description: Please find detailed information in PDF documentation.

name: hgroom
label: Number Of Rooms Larger than 6 Square Meters
description:
The procedure of carrying forward and imputation is identical to that for HGSIZE. In the regression model the same covariates are used with the exception of HGROOM which is replaced with HGSIZE (size of the housing unit in square meters). In case information on HGSIZE is missing, a first imputation was done excluding HGSIZE. In case information for HGSIZE exists, these values were replaced with values obtained from a second imputation including HGSIZE as a covariate.   

In case HGROOM is imputed, the flag variable HGFROOM takes the value “1”.

This information is not assessed in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample from 2012 on, therefore this variable is not generated for these years and coded to "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: hgheat
label: Costs Of Warm Water (gen)
description: This information is not assessed in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample from 2012 on, therefore this variable is not generated for these years and coded to "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: hgutil
label: Cost Allocation (gen)
description:
HGRENT, HGUTIL and HGHEAT are generated variables on the housing cost of households in rental properties. HGRENT is a measure of the gross rent including utility costs (HGUTIL) and excluding heating costs (HGHEAT).

For further  information on HGRENT, HGUTIL and HGHEAT please see the corresponding SOEP HGEN documentation.

name: hgrent
label: Amount of Rent Minus Heating Costs (EUR)
description:
Because detailed information on heating costs is not assessed
 in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample, in the
 years 2011 and 2012 HGRENT was generated by simply duplicating
 respondents’ answers on the amount of monthly rent from the H
 dataset.

name: hgelectr
label: Costs of Electricity (gen)
description:
Information was collected in wave BA (2010) for the first time. The procedure of imputation is identical to that for HGHEAT. In the regression model the same covariates are used.
 
In case HGELECTR is imputed, the flag variable HGFELECTR takes the value “1”. In the year 2011, no imputation of HGELECTR was conducted.

This information is not assessed in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample from 2012 on, therefore this variable is not generated for these years and coded to "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: hgnorent
label: Does Not Pay Rent
description:
Coded as “1” if the household does not pay rent; e.g., if living space is provided by relatives at no cost. Note that in these cases, the information on gross cold rent (HGRENT), heating costs (HGHEAT) and utilities (HGUTIL) is coded “-2” (“not applicable”).

 Information is not carried forward.

name: hgfsize
label: Imputation Flag, Size Of Housing
description: This variable contains information, whether the refering variable has been imputed. If the refering information has not been assessed in the questionnaire, this flag also contains "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: hgfroom
label: Imputation Flag, Number Of Rooms Lager than 6 Square Meters
label_de: Imputation Flag, Zahl der Wohnräume über 6 qm
description: This variable contains information, whether the refering variable has been imputed. If the refering information has not been assessed in the questionnaire, this flag also contains "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: hgfheat
label: Imputation Flag, Costs Of Heating And Warm Water
description: This variable contains information, whether the refering variable has been imputed. If the refering information has not been assessed in the questionnaire, this flag also contains "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: hgfutil
label: Imputation Flag, Cost Allocation
description:
Please note that HGFUTIL is also given the value “1” for households reporting that utility costs are only partly included in the amount of rent stated (see the description of HGUTIL).

This variable contains information, whether the refering variable has been imputed. If the refering information has not been assessed in the questionnaire, this flag also contains "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: hgfrent
label: Imputation Flag, Amount Of Rent Minus Heating Costs
description: Please find detailed information in PDF documentation.

name: hgfelectr
label: Imputation Flag, Costs of Electricity
description: This variable contains information, whether the refering variable has been imputed. If the refering information has not been assessed in the questionnaire, this flag also contains "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: hgtyp1hh
label: Household Typology, One Digit
description:
Generated variable created by combining the relationships of all persons living in the household to the head of household (Variable $STELL in the file PBRUTTO) at the time of the survey.

From 2009 onwards, the data production process switched to a standardized procedure for all waves to ensure longitudinal consistency, resulting in minor changes compared with older distributions.

HGTYP1HH is an aggregation of HGTYP2HH (first column of the two-digit code). Single households are differentiated in HGTYP2HH according to both gender and age.

Due to a slightly modified $STELL variable in the file PBRUTTO, the generation syntax of HGTYP1HH and HGTYP2HH needed to be updated in the year 2011.

 Legend:  

• LE = less or equal

• GT = greater than

• K = child

name: hghmode

name: hghinc

name: hgahinc
label: Adjusted Monthly Household Net Income (EUR)
description: Please find detailed information in PDF documentation.

name: hgnuts1
label: NUTS-Systematic-1 (Federal State)
description: NUTS ("Nomenclature of Statistical Territorial Units") is a hierarchical system for dividing up the economic territory of the European Union. It was introduced by Eurostat more than 30 years ago in order to provide a single uniform breakdown of territorial units for the production of regional statistics. NUTS 1 especially contains the major socio-economic regions for analyzing regional Community problems. It subdivides the European Union by now into 97 regions, whereas in Germany there are equivalent to the German Federal States 16 regions.

name: hgfhinc

description: HGFHINC is a dummy variable indicating whether an observation was missing on HGHINC and was therefore imputed or not.

name: spa1
label: When someone does me a favor, I am ready to return it
label_de: Wenn mir jemand einen Gefallen tut, bin ich bereit, ihn zu erwidern

name: spa2
label: If I experience a great injustice, I will take revenge
label_de: Wenn mir ein schweres Unrecht zuteil wird, werde ich mich rächen

name: spa3
label: If someone gets me in trouble, I will do the same to them
label_de: Wenn mich jemand in schwierige Lage bringt, werde ich das auch mit ihm tun

name: spa4
label: I make a special effort when helping someone who has helped me before
label_de: Ich strenge mich an, um jemandem zu helfen, der mir schon mal geholfen hat

name: spa5
label: When someone insults me, I will be rude to them as well
label_de: Wenn mich jemand beleidigt, werde ich ihm ggü. auch beleidigend

name: spa6
label: I am ready to invest time in helping someone who has helped me before
label_de: Ich bin bereit, Zeit zu investieren, um jem. zu helfen, der mir geholfen hat

name: spa7
label: When I am in an unfamiliar place, I often feel insecure / unsafe
label_de: Wenn ich in einer ungewohnten Umgebung bin, fühle ich mich oft unsicher

name: spa8
label: When given a difficult task, I am confident that I will succeed
label_de: Bei einer schweren Aufgabe bin ich sicher, sie gut meistern zu werden

name: spa9
label: I am someone who thinks of him/herself as capable
label_de: Ich bin jemand, der sich etwas zutraut

name: spa10
label: I believe that I will achieve much in my life
label_de: Ich glaube, dass ich im Leben viel erreichen werde

name: spa11
label: I believe that I will have a good and interesting job
label_de: Ich glaube, dass ich einmal einen guten, interessanten Beruf haben werde

name: spa12
label: I believe that I will earn a lot of money someday
label_de: Ich glaube, dass ich einmal viel Geld verdienen werde

name: spa13
label: When something can go right or wrong, I expect it to go right
label_de: Wenn etwas gut oder schlecht laufen kann, glaube ich eher, dass es gut wird

name: spa14
label: I believe that, all in all, more good than bad things happen to me
label_de: Ich glaube, dass mir insgesamt eher gute als schlechte Dinge passieren

name: spa15
label: When something can go wrong for me, I believe that it will go wrong
label_de: Wenn etw. für mich schief gehen kann, glaube ich, dass es schief gehen wird

name: spa16
label: I believe that you can succeed in every school subject if you learn a lot
label_de: Ich glaube, man kann durch viel Lernen in jedem Fach in der Schule gut sein

name: spa17
label: What you achieve in life is mainly a matter of fate or luck
label_de: Was man im Leben erreicht, ist vor allem eine Frage von Schicksal oder Glück

name: spa18
label: When I have a goal I make special efforts to achieve it
label_de: Wenn ich ein Ziel habe, strenge ich mich sehr an, um es zu erreichen

name: spa19
label: I always wear a helmet when riding the bicycle
label_de: Ich trage beim Fahrradfahren immer einen Helm

name: spa20
label: I often cross the street despite red traffic lights
label_de: Ich gehe oft bei Rot über die Ampel

name: muelj1
label: Because my contribution to garbage separation counts.
label_de: Weil auch mein eigener Beitrag zur Mülltrennung zählt.

name: muelj2
label: Because one should separate the garbage.
label_de: Weil man seinen Müll trennen sollte.

name: muelj3
label: Because I would have a bad conscience if I did not separate my garbage.
label_de: Weil ich ein schlechtes Gewissen hätte, wenn ich Müll nicht trennen würde

name: muelj4
label: Because I want to set a good example.
label_de: Weil ich als gutes Beispiel vorangehen möchte.

name: muelj5
label: Because separating garbage helps keeping the household tidy.
label_de: Weil das Trennen von Müll für Ordnung im Haushalt sorgt.

name: muelj6
label: Because people in my neighbourhood separate their garbage.
label_de: Weil die Menschen in meiner Nachbarschaft auch ihren Müll trennen.

name: muelj7
label: Because garbage collection is more expensive if I do not separate.
label_de: Weil die Müllabholung teurer wird, wenn ich den Müll nicht trenne.

name: mueln1
label: Because it makes no difference if I separate or not.
label_de: Weil es keinen Unterschied macht, ob ich meinen Müll trenne oder nicht.

name: mueln2
label: Because there is no reason to separate one‘s garbage.
label_de: Weil es keinen Grund gibt, seinen Müll zu trennen.

name: mueln3
label: Because I do not care whether my garbage is separated.
label_de: Weil es mir egal ist, ob mein Müll getrennt wird oder nicht.

name: mueln4
label: Because the costs of garbage separation outrun the advantages.
label_de: Weil die Kosten des Trennens von Müll höher als die Vorteile sind.

name: mueln5
label: Because garbage separation is too time-consuming.

name: mueln6
label: Because people in my neighbourhood do not separate their garbage either.
label_de: Weil die Menschen in meiner Nachbarschaft ihren Müll auch nicht trennen.

name: mueln7
label: Because garbage collection is not more expensive if I do not separate.
label_de: Weil Müllabholung auch nicht wesentl. teurer wird, wenn ich Müll nicht trenne

name: pid
label: ID Of Child
description: Unique person identifier for each person in the SOEP-IS database.

name: syear
label: Survey Year
description: Variable SYEAR represents the year of observation. It ranges from 1998 to the most recent wave of data. SYEAR is needed in conjunction with PID for unique identification of a PERSON-YEAR observation in KID.

name: k_samp
label: Sample Membership
description: Variable K_SAMP depicts the sample membership of each child and is a copy of variable PSAMPLE from data  file PPFAD.

name: k_rel
label: Relationship To Head Of Household
description: variable K_REL indicates the wave-specific relationship of the child to head of household and can be found as variable STELL in  file PBRUTTO. The values (1) and (2) should by definition not be relevant in the file KID.

name: k_inhh
label: Member Of Household
description: variable K_INHH indicates the wave-specific houshold affiliation of a child and can be found as $PZUG in the  file $PBRUTTO. The values (19) and (39) have been recoded in the  file $KIDLONG, and are now assigned code "-1" (no answer).

name: k_size
label: Household Size
description: Variable K_SIZE is a copy of the variable HHGR from the file HBRUTTO.

name: k_nrkid
label: Number Of Children In Household
label_de: Zahl der Kinder unter 16 Jahren im HH
description: For each child in KID the variable K_NRKID provides the total number of children up to the age 16 in the current wave's household.

name: k_phead
label: Pointer To Head Of Household
description: Generated as PID of the head of household, i.e. person with STELL = 0 in the file PBRUTTO.

name: k_pheadp
label: Pointer To Partner Of Head
description: PID of the partner of the head of household. K_PHEADP combines information of STELL in the file PBRUTTO with the partner information taken from the variable PARTNR in file PGEN.

name: k_pmum
label: Pointer To Mother
description: PID of a child's mother. The procedure for generating the pointers was modified to define the mother-child relationship as a combination of the variables STELL (=relationship to household head) and PARTNR (=person ID number of spouse or partner). The information of PARTNR in file PGEN is only available when an interview took place with the partner. If this data is lacking the combination of relationship to household head of the mother and of the mother's partner is used. Further information on the definition of social/biological mother-child relationships in the SOEP can be found in the BIO documentation for the  file $BIOBIRTH.

name: k_pmump
label: Pointer To Partner Of Mother
description: PID of the partner of the child's mother (cf. PARTNR of the mother in the person-related  file PGEN).

name: ks_pre
label: Pre-School
description: In order to integrate various information on formal childcare from all waves of the SOEP into one variable KS_PRE, the different codes of different questionnaire items were modifed. For the waves O to BB (1998-2011) the value "1" indicates the answer "yes, nursery school". Children who do not attend formal childcare in waves O to BB (1998-2011) are coded "-2" in variable KS_PRE and can be found in variable KS_NONE (see description below).

name: ks_gen
label: General Education System
description: The variable KS_PRE summarize information about the general school education.

name: ks_vocat
label: Vocational School
description: Variable KS_VOCAT describes vocational school participation in addition to KS_GEN in order to represent the different instruments in the waves O to Z. In fact, the dataset does not contain any valid cases.

name: ks_none
label: None Of These Institutions
description: Variable KS_NONE collects missing information for the variables KS_PRE and KS_GEN. For KS_NONE value  "1" to  "3" describes whether children do not attend preschool KS_PRE or do not attend any general schools stored in KS_GEN.

name: ks_east
label: General School East Germany
description: Variable KS_EAST summarizes additional school type information collected in the SOEP waves G and H (1990/91) in East Germany. Therefore, this information KS_EAST is not available for SOEP-IS.

name: ks_eastp
label: Day-Home For School Children,East
description: Variable KS_EASTP summarizes additional preschool information collected in waves G and H (1990/91) in East Germany. Therefore, this information KS_EASTP is not available for SOEP-IS.

name: ks_other
label: Other Type Of School
description: Variable KS_OTHER summarizes additional school type information collected in wave L and M (1995/96). Therefore, this information KS_OTHER is not available for SOEP-IS.

name: kd_publ
label: Public Institution
description: Variable KD_PUBL summarizes information collected in the years 2002, 2005, 2007 and 2011. This information KS_PUBL is not available for the survey years of SOEP-IS.

name: kd_priv
label: Private Provider Of Facility
description: Variable KD_PRIV summarizes information collected in the years 2002, 2005, 2007 and 2011. Therefore, this information KS_PRIV is not available for the survey years of SOEP-IS.

name: kd_indep
label: Independent Provider Of Facility
description: Variable KD_INDEP summarizes information collected in the years 2002, 2005, 2007 and 2011. Therefore, this information KS_INDEP is not available for the survey years of SOEP-IS.

name: kd_comp
label: Company Facility
description: Variable KD_COMP summarizes information collected in the years 2002, 2005, 2007 and 2011. Therefore, this information KS_COMP is not available for the survey years of SOEP-IS.

name: kd_comm
label: Commercial Provider Of Facility
description: Variable KD_COMM summarizes information collected in the years 2002, 2005, 2007 and 2011. Therefore, this information KS_COMM is not available for the survey years of SOEP-IS.

name: kd_time
label: Time Of Day Of Care
description: Variable KD_TIME specifically asks whether a child attends the school full time or not (see SOEP KS_GEN). The institutions are preschool, crèche and nursery (also after nursery school). The information KS_TIME is not available for the survey years of SOEP-IS.

name: kd_hrs
label: Hours P.Day Spent At Facility
label_de: Stunden pro Tag in der Einrichtung
description: Variable KD_HRS contains information on how many hours per day a child attends an institution and has been introduced in the SOEP in 2009. The institutions are preschool, crèche and nursery (also after school nursery). The information KD_HRS is not available for the survey years of SOEP-IS.

name: kd_rely
label: Adherence To Opening Time
description: Variable KD_RELY comprises information on the adherence to opening times of day care facilities and was only collected in wave S of the SOEP Data.

name: kd_lunch
label: Lunch At Facility
description: Variable KD_LUNCH contains information collected in the years 2002, 2005, 2007 and 2011. Therefore, this information KS_LUNCH is not available for the survey years of SOEP-IS.

name: kd_fee
label: Fee Payable For Attendance
description: Variable KD_FEE summarizes observations of the years 2002, 2005 and 2007. Therefore, this information KS_FEE is not available for the survey years of SOEP-IS.

name: kd_amtp
label: Amount Paid
description: If parents pay a fixed sum in EURO KD_AMTP comprises the actual amount paid. This information KS_AMTP is only available for the years 2002, 2005 and 2007.

name: kc_relat
label: Carer: Relatives
description: Variable KC_RELAT summarizes information collected in the years 1999 to 2002, 2004 to 2011. Therefore, this information KS_RELAT is not available for the survey years of SOEP-IS. More detailed information can be found in SOEP KIDLONG documentation.

name: kc_frnd
label: Carer: Friends
description: Variable KC_FRND comprises information available from waves Z and BA, observing that a child is an informal care provided by friends, neighbors, etc..

name: kc_paid
label: Carer: Paid
description: Variable KC_PAID comprises information available of the years 1999 to 2002, 2004 to 2011, observing that a child is in informal care provided by paid carers, i.e. nannies and babysitters.

name: kc_mindr
label: Carer: Child Minder
description: Variable KC_MINDR comprises information available from the years 1998 to 2011, observing that a child is in care provided by a child minder.

name: kc_none
label: Carer: None
description: Variable KC_NONE collects the missing information for variables KC_RELAT-KC_MINDR. It comprises all information available observing that a child is not using informal care.

name: kc_amtp
label: External Care: Costs per Month
label_de: externe Betreuung: durchschnittl. Kosten pro Monat
description:
In wave BB (2011) another aspect of monthly costs was surveyed: How much do the above mentioned care arrangements outside the household cost? Parents indicate
average monthly cost of their children regarding additional care outside the household, e.g., relatives, friends, neighbors, etc.. This item is not available for the survey years of SOEP-IS.

name: kc_cost
label: External Care: No Costs
description: Corresponding to parents' estimation of average monthly costs  "no costs" indicates if parents do not have any costs. This item is introduced in 2011, wave BB, but is not available for the survey years of SOEP-IS.

name: ka06_non
label: No Activities Under 6
description: Variable KA06_NON indicates that a child does not participate in any activities for children below the age of 6.

name: ka16_non
label: No Activities Above 6
description: Variable KA16_NON indicates that a child does not participate in any activities for children above the age of 6.

name: k_amtp
label: Average Costs Per Month
description: The variable K_AMTP describes the costs of school, care and activities. In wave BA (2010) average monthly costs were surveyed: How much do the above mentioned school, care and activities cost you? Parents indicate average monthly cost of their children regarding school, care, and (leisure) activities, e.g., early music education, sports, etc.. In wave BA this variable was surveyed for the last time. Other than variable KD_AMTP, the variable K_AMTP indentifies overall average monthly costs and not just day care fees. This variable is not available for the survey years of SOEP-IS.

name: k_cost
label: No Costs
description: Corresponding to parents' estimation of average monthly costs K_AMTP  "no costs" indicates if parents do not have any costs.

description: Please find detailed information in PDF documentation.

name: pgerljob
label: Working in Occupation Trained for
description:
This variable is designed to offer annual data on all employed persons, indicating whether they are working in the occupation they were trained for.

Not all employed persons are asked the relevant input questions on an annual basis. Only those employed persons who changed jobs and first-time respondents were asked to provide up-to-date information.
 
Because detailed information on working in occupation trained for is not assessed in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample, PGERLJOB is not generated for Sample E (since 2012), I (since 2011) and the supplementary samples (since 2012). For this purpose, PGERLJOB is coded to "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: pgbetr
label: Size of the Company
description:
This variable is designed to offer annual data on company size for all employed persons.
 Please pay attention to special codes 4, 5, and 8! These codes were necessary due to the differentiation of items for small and medium-sized companies over the years.
 
Not all employed persons are asked the question on firm size on an annual basis. Only those employed persons who changed jobs and first-time respondents were asked to provide up-to-date information.
  
Please also see PGALLBET for a broader categorization of the firm size, which is appropriate for analyses that include all sample years.

Self-employed are not included in this variable. Detailed information about the company size of self-employed is included in the variable PGSTIB.

name: pgoeffd
label: Civil Service
description:
This variable is designed to provide annual data on employment in the civil service for all employed persons.

Not all employed persons are asked the relevant input questions on an annual basis. Only those employed persons who changed jobs and first-time respondents were asked to provide up-to-date information.

name: pgpartz
label: Partner Identicator
description: Please find detailed information in PDF documentation.

name: pgpartnr
label: Person ID number of partner
description:
Partner indicators have the purpose of clearly defining spouse (married) and partner (unmarried) relationships in SOEP households and thus to make possible analyses on the couple level.

If PGPARTZ is coded 0 or 9, this person has no partner or the partner cannot be identified as such. The variable PGPARTNR is assigned the missing code of “-2” (=does not apply) for these persons.

If PGPARTZ is coded 1, 2, 3 or 4, a partnership was defined and PGPARTNR is then assigned the value of the unchanging person ID number (=PERSNR) of the partner.

For analyses of partner relationships, this information can be used to clearly link all persons with their respective partners, and all information on both partners can also be stored in a common dataset.

name: pgnation
label: Citizenship - nationality
description: This variable is designed to integrate the information on respondents’ nationality for all subsamples.

name: pgsbil
label: Diplomas/degrees from secondary/tertiary
description:
All respondents in all SOEP subsamples are asked about diplomas/degrees attained for completion of secondary/tertiary education the first time they participate in SOEP.
 
As the SOEP Innovation Sample does not include a youth questionnaire, since 2012 information usually coming from the youth questionnaire was not included in the generation of PGSBIL.

name: pgbbil01
label: Vocational degree attained
description:
All respondents in all subsamples are asked about vocational degrees attained the first time they participate in SOEP. The categories that originally each constituted individual variables are combined to make them compatible with the annual question about changes in vocational degrees attained, and this data is updated annually.

Since the SOEP Innovation Sample does not include a youth questionnaire, the information usually coming from the youth questionnaire was not included in the generation of PGBBIL01.

name: pgbbil02
label: Completed college education
description:
All respondents in all subsamples are asked about completed college education the first time they participate in SOEP. To generate the variable, the different degrees/diplomas for all subsamples are integrated. Category (3) “college abroad” is only defined for persons who completed a foreign-language version of the questionnaire. Generation of the variable entails combining the categories to make them compatible with the annual question about changes in vocational degrees/diplomas attained.

Since the SOEP Innovation Sample does not include a youth questionnaire, the information usually coming from the youth questionnaire was not included in the generation of PGBBIL02.

name: pgbbil03
label: No vocational degree
description:
In connection with the question about vocational degrees (PGBBIL01 and PGBBIL02), all first-time respondents to all subsamples are explicitly asked whether they (still) do not possess a vocational degree. In the subsequent years, this data is carried forward or updated. The variable has the Missing Value Code -2 (does not apply) if one of the other two variables on vocational degree has a positive value.

Since the SOEP Innovation Sample does not include a youth questionnaire, the information usually coming from the youth questionnaire was not included in the generation of PGBBIL03.

name: pgsbila
label: Secondary school degrees/diplomas abroad
description:
As a supplement to the PGSBIL, this variable provides annually updated data on the highest secondary school degree/diploma attained abroad.

Since the SOEP Innovation Sample does not include a youth questionnaire, the information usually coming from the youth questionnaire was not included in the generation of PGSBILA.

name: pgbbila
label: Occupational Training in abroad
description:
As a supplement to the variable PGBBIL01, this variable gives (and updates) the highest-level vocational degree attained abroad.

Because detailed information on occupational training abroad is not assessed in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample, PGBBILA is not generated for Sample E (since 2012), I (since 2011) and the supplementary samples (since 2012). For this purpose, PGBBILA is coded to "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: pgsbilo
label: Secondary school degree/diploma - East Germany
description:
As a supplement to the variable PGSBIL the highest secondary school degree/diploma in East Germany is provided as a separate variable.

New SOEP respondents are also asked about secondary degrees/diplomas obtained in the former GDR; and for old respondents, the same codes are carried forward.

As SOEP-IS does not include a youth questionnaire, since 2012 information usually coming from the youth questionnaire was not included in the generation of PGSBILO.

name: pgtatzt
label: Actual Weekly Work Time
description:
This variable is designed to offer annual data on actual weekly working hours (including overtime) for all persons employed at the time of the survey (including the self-employed). The data are obtained by asking respondents how many hours they work on average per week.
              
For implausible answers (actual weekly working hours of more than 80 per week), we assign the value (-3).
 The variable is rounded off and gives the number of working hours as a decimal number.
 
Please also see PGVEBZT and PGUEBSTD.

name: pgsiops88
label: TREIMANS STANDARD INT.OCC.PR.SCORE (based on IS88)
description:
This variable gives the occupational prestige score index for all employed persons. PGSIOPS is based on ISCO-88 and was developed by Donald Treiman et al. The scale ranges from 6 to 78.

Not all employed persons are asked the relevant input questions on an annual basis. Only those employed persons who changed jobs and first-time respondents were asked to provide up-to-date information.  
 
Please also see occupational prestige scores (pgmps92), occupational status (pgisei88), and occupational class (pgegp88).

In the SOEP-IS, pgsiops88 is released up until 2016 and coded to [-5] afterwards. Starting in 2017, only pgsiops08 scores will be released.

name: pgcasmin

description: As an alternative to PGISCED, a second educational variable is generated (PGCASMIN) that also enables comparison with international educational degrees/diplomas. Based on the modified CASMIN classification scheme (Comparative Analysis of Social Mobility in Industrial Nations), this variable has been computed retroactively from 1984 on for all respondents. name: pgallbet
label: Core size category of the company
description:
This variable is designed to provide annual data on the core size category of the company for all employed persons.
 
Not all employed persons are asked the relevant input questions on an annual basis. Only those employed persons who changed jobs and first-time respondents were asked to provide up-to-date information.

Self-employed are not included in this variable. Information about the company size is included in the variable pgstib.

name: pgemplst
label: Employment status
description:
This variable is generated from the annual question on current employment status, which has a central filter function in the questionnaire to separate employed people from non-employed people for further questions. It is designed to provide consistent longitudinal data on employment status across all waves.
 
The category “not employed” comprises non-working individuals, those in military/community service, those on maternity leave, and employed persons in a phased retirement scheme (Altersteilzeit) whose current actual working hours are zero.

PGEMPLST supplements the variable PGLFS, which differentiates among persons who are not employed.

description:
The variable is designed to provide information on the occupation of full-time school based vocational training (e.g., Berufsfachschule, Schule des Gesundheitswesens, Handelsschule). See the description of variable PGTRAINA for more details on the construction and the values of the variable.

Because detailed information on the specific fields of occupation is not assessed in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample, PGTRAINB is not generated for Sample E (since 2012), I (since 2011) and the supplementary samples (since 2012). For this purpose, PGTRAINB is coded to "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: pgtrainc
label: Higher vocational school, two-digit occupation KldB92
description:
The variable is designed to provide information on the occupation of higher level vocational training (e.g., Meister, Techniker). See the description of variable PGTRAINA for more details on the construction and the values of the variable.

Because detailed information on the specific fields of occupation is not assessed in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample, PGTRAINC is not generated for Sample E (since 2012), I (since 2011) and the supplementary samples (since 2012). For this purpose, PGTRAINC is coded to "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: pgtraind
label: Civil servant training, two-digit occupation KldB92
description:
The variable is designed to provide information on the occupation of civil servant training (“Beamtenausbildung”). See the description of variable PGTRAINA for more details on the construction and the values of the variable.

Because detailed information on the specific fields of occupation is not assessed in the Questionnaire of the SOEP Innovation Sample, PGTRAIND is not generated for Sample E (since 2012), I (since 2011) and the supplementary samples (since 2012). For this purpose, PGTRAIND is coded to "-5" (not contained in questionnaire).

name: todinfo
label: Year Died, Information Source
description:
For all persons who have been identified as deceased over the course of SOEP, the variable TODINFO gives the source of this information. The variable TODJAHR contains the four-digit year of death or a missing value code:

 (-2): persons, for whom it is unknown whether they are deceased (that is, both persons still living up to that wave, and persons whose exact whereabouts is unknown and have dropped out of SOEP-IS)

 (-1): persons, for whom the fact of death is known, but the year of death is unknown.

 $$$$: factual year of death for persons whose death could be firmly established

 The information is taken from the annual survey or/and the question about family events in the personal questionnaire.

name: loc1989
label: Where did you live in 1989?
description:
This variable's information is mainly based upon the corresponding question in the biography questionnaire. Additionally, persons who ansered 'East Germany' or 'West Germany' but stated that they immigrated after 1989 were corrected to '[3] Abroad'. Persons who initially answered 'Abroad' but also stated that they immigrated to Germany before 1989 were corrected to '[-3] Answer Improbable'.
 
For individuals with the values '[-1] No Answer' or '[-2] Does Not Apply' no valid information could be generated. Note that '[-2] Does Not Apply' is assigned to adults who never answered an individual questionnaire. Persons with NETTO$ codes between 210 and 229 are coded to '[-1] No Answer' if relevant information is missing.

name: pop98
label: Sample Membership 1998
description:
POP$ was derived from $WUM2 (see private household, institutional household in $HBRUTTO) as well as $PNAT and $STELL (nationality and relationship to head of household in $PBRUTTO). Missing values were imputed based on the person’s history. Thus, the only admissible missing value is –2, meaning not applicable.

This variable is therefore particularly important, as it enters into the determination of cross-sectional weights.

POP$ was derived from $WUM2 (see private household, institutional household in $HBRUTTO) as well as $PNAT and $STELL (nationality and relationship to head of household in $PBRUTTO). Missing values were imputed based on the person’s history. Thus, the only admissible missing value is –2, meaning not applicable.

This variable is therefore particularly important, as it enters into the determination of cross-sectional weights.

name: sampreg98
label: Current Sample Region 1998
description:
Households have been identified as living in either in the West or the East sample region. This information is time-dependent; thus for each year, there is the wave-specific information SAMPREG$.

 For analyses differentiating between East and West Germany, the current sample region variable SAMPREG$ should be used, and not the time-independent original sample variable PSAMPLE.

name: casemat98
label: Case Match, Combined Panel Households 1998
description:
For Wave 2010 of SOEP-IS, we had two individuals from different original households (CASES) living in one common household. In this case, people with identical values for HID in one wave have different values for CID (CASE-ID).

The CASEMAT$ variable is assigned a value only for those persons living in the households described above, and contains the CID of the other household members.

This information is not relevant when linking person and household data based on the current household number HID in non-hierarchically structured databanks.
